<project-description>
Here we creating event tracking app, visually slightly similar with GitHub commits calendar, but with purpose of tracking events of the day manually.

<screen-1 name="Main Screen" title="Events">On this screen user can see calendar of user's life, as a "GitHub commits chart"-like matrix where each square is a one day. Size of squares should be appropriate to show approximately 30-50 days on the screen. Square should be visually grouped by week, month. User can scroll calendar infinitely to past and future. Each row  of the calendar should contain 7 cell, where days of the week placed as follows: monday, tuesday, wednesday, thursday, friday, saturday, sunday</screen-1>
<screen-2 name="Settings" title="Settings">On this screen, user should be able to edit list of legend categories for the main screen. User should be able to create/edit/delete legend categories here. Create - plus icon button right bottom corner. Edit/delete - "pencil"/"trash" icon buttons for the each item. Each legend category has name, description and color.</screen-2>

<feature-1>User can click to any square to fill it. When user clicks on square on main screen, popup appears, where user can see exact date of that square, like "2025-11-25", selector to choose legend category, and selector to choose "approx. duration" - from list: whole day, half a day, 1/4 of day. When user fill all the data, press "Save" and such square should be colored in color of legend category. If 1/2, 1/4 or 1/8 of day choosen, then only 1/2-1/8 of such square should be colored. Square parts should be colored from top to bottom (when several legend categories choosen for one day, with 1/2 or 1/8 duration).</feature-1>
</project-description>
